<%= render partial: 'shared/header' %>
<div class='intro-to-tws cover-photo'>
  <div class='content'>
    <div class='content-box'>
      <h2 class='cover-photo-lede'>
        Expand your world, one 
        real-life conversation at a time.
      </h2>
      <button class='orange cover-photo-cta'>
        <%= link_to 'Sign Up', '#' %>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<%#= render partial: 'shared/press_list', locals: {items: @press}%>
<div class="tea-explainers container">
  <div class="tea-explainer">
    <%= image_tag 'landing/1.png', class: ['right', 'tea-explainer-illustration'] %>
    <div class="tea-explainer-copy left">
    	<h3 class="tea-explainer-header">
    	  You don’t know most of the people around you
    	</h3>
    	<p class="tea-explainer-body">
    	  And current ways of meeting new people suck. There’s usually strings
    	  attached, like a business deal or a date. Most conversations never make it
    	  past happy hour talk of “what do you do?” You never get to talk about
    	  anything real. About anything that makes us who we are. But what if there
    	  was a different way?
    	</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="tea-explainer">
    <%= image_tag 'landing/2.png', class: ['left', 'tea-explainer-illustration'] %>
    <div class="tea-explainer-copy right">
    	<h3 class="tea-explainer-header">Tea times create space for good
    	  conversations with good people
    	</h3>
    	<p class="tea-explainer-body">
    	  Five to six strangers get together, sit down, and have a conversation
    	  about, well, anything and everything. There’s a host who keeps things just
    	  awkward enough. If you make friends, cool. If you don’t, cool.  
    	</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="tea-explainer">
    <%= image_tag 'landing/3.png', class: ['right', 'tea-explainer-illustration'] %>
    <div class="tea-explainer-copy left">
    	<h3 class="tea-explainer-header">Because why not? People are freaking awesome.</h3>
    	<p class="tea-explainer-body">
    	  When you’re around strangers, you can be yourself. There’s no presumption
    	  about who you are; you could legit be anyone you want to be. What’s the best
    	  that could happen? It’s out of everybody’s comfort zone, but you’ll meet
    	  people you may have never encountered otherwise.
    	</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="cta-footer cover-photo">
  <div class='content'>
    <div class='content-box'>
      <h2>
        Ready to take the plunge?
      </h2>
      <button class='orange cover-photo-cta'>
        <%= link_to 'Sign Up', '#' %>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
